Description:
Delivery Partner to Insight Direct UK Limited

Birmingham City Council (the Council) is intending to enter into a contract extension with Insight Direct UK Limited (Insight) for the provision of structured cabling, AV and digital signage services. Insight will be acting as the prime contractor for the services however they will be delivered directly to the Council by Delivery Partners under sub-contact to Insight with the relevant core capabilities, knowledge and skills.

Expressions of interest (EOI) are being sought from additional providers, particularly SME's local to Birmingham who would be interested in becoming a Delivery Partner to Insight and are in a position to provide BCC with the following services:

• Installation of structured cabling (copper and fibre) and associated cabinets, power and ancillary services;
• Installation of wireless access points including mounting and associated cabling;
• Testing and repair of existing installations as required;
• Site surveys to determine the scope of work and associated price for the purpose of bidding for work packages;
• Wireless site surveys, including heat maps, both desktop and physical;
• Point to point wireless / laser / microwave connectivity;
• Supply of associated consumables such as media converters, copper and fibre patch leads, power adapters, couplers and other similar hardware;
• Audio-Visual equipment to support video conferencing and digital signage; and
• Support and maintenance of the above.

To be selected as a Delivery Partner, BCC / Insight will require the following to be provided as a minimum:

• Information relating to your core service capabilities;
• Relevant and recent experience in delivering the services described above;
• Confirmation that you are formally registered as a legal contracting entity at Companies House;
• Confirmation that your regular filed accounts indicate financial stability and you would be happy to submit published accounts to Insight for review; and
• Confirmation that you are happy to sign up to the Insight Partner Agreement if selected.

Providers that wish to express interest in becoming a valued Delivery Partner should email jamie.parris@birmingham.gov.uk and shaun.brooks@insight.com  on or before 17:00 on Friday 25th April 2025

The scope of the Subsubcontract works is the provision of all necessary People, Equipment, Plant, Materials, methodology, design and detailing for the fit out and decoration works inside the envelope line as per the accompanying drawings and specifications. The works also include all required temporary works (if any), and their design, installation of, ongoing maintenance of and removal required for the safe execution of the Subsubcontract works. The end product needs to comply with the acoustics and fire performance requirements as stated in the documentation which forms part of this scope. 

      The scope includes, but is not limited to, the following works:

      •	Internal Wall Systems (excluding glazed systems), dry lining, shaft walls, stud partitions, bulk heads, roller shutters and IPS panelling including wall access hatches in the vertical plane. Internal wall systems to include suitable support to doors (IWS);
      •	Acoustic Lining (AL);
      •	Security Lining* (SL);
      •	Raised Access Flooring systems including access hatches and outlets (RAF);
      •	Suspended Ceilings (SC)
      •	Formation and fitout of offices, toilets, and kitchenettes (Office)
      •	Fixtures, Fittings & Equipment (FF&E)
      •	Wall and floor coverings including, but not limited to, ceramic tiles, ceramic wall laminate, rubber flooring, skirtings, internal DPM flashings, corduroy/tactile warning surfaces etc (COV);
      •	Wall, floor, soffit, stair and ramp finishes including, but not limited to, sealer, paint, resin and internal mastic works excluding intumescent mastic to doors and windows (PAINT).
      •	Screeding, insulation and DPM works to buildings excluding West Core, East Core, North Portal, South Portal and OOC Interface Substation (SCREED)

The Contract is to increase capacity in support of  (SCC) in-house teams in delivering voids, major works, planned works, disrepair works, response repairs & minor works to residential dwellings, civic buildings, and other properties, sites and assets owned, managed or leased by SCC; all to agreed standards and in a timely, consistent, cost effective and safe manner. 
      A more detailed description of the services required are detailed within this suite of documents but the categories/workstreams included within this tendering opportunity comprise:- 

      •	Voids 
      •	General Building & Maintenance Works; 
      •	Roofing Repairs; 
      •	Scaffolding; 
      •	Glazing & Window Repairs; 
      •	Drainage Surveys, Clearance & Repairs; 
      •	Flooring; 
      •	Locksmiths; 
      •	Carpentry; 
      •	Damp-proofing, Timber Treatment & Associated Repairs; 
      •	Electrical Installation & Repairs; 
      •	Gas & Heating Installation & Repairs;  
      •	Minor Civil Engineering & Groundworks; 
      •	Brickwork/Stonework & Associated Repairs;
